OL,3,CWage pressures pushing UK firms to
OL,4,Cautomate more work, Hays says
OL,6,FBut it said there were several
OL,7,Fspecific challenges facing the UK that
OL,8,Fwas making it a less competitive place
OL,9,Ffor work.
OL,11,FTom Way, its UK and Ireland chief
OL,12,Fexecutive, said: "The UK is a great
OL,13,Fplace to work if you are an employee
OL,14,Fbut it's becoming more unattractive to
OL,15,Fhire people permanently.
OL,17,F"Wage pressures and national insurance
OL,18,Fchanges are pushing employers to
OL,19,Fexplore automation and offshoring."
