OL,3,CWage pressures pushing UK firms to
OL,4,Cautomate more work, Hays says
OL,6,FThe national minimum wage rose in
OL,7,FApril, boosting pay for many workers
OL,8,Fbut driving up labour costs for
OL,9,Femployers.
OL,11,FIt came on top of many businesses
OL,12,Fhaving to increase their national
OL,13,Finsurance contributions as a result of
OL,14,Ftax changes outlined in last year's
OL,15,Fbudget.
OL,17,FHays said the cost pressures have
OL,18,Fpushed companies to think about work
OL,19,Fwhere "humans are essential" and then
OL,20,Fdigitalising or outsourcing the rest.
